{"title_page": "Jack Conte", "text_new": "{{Short description|American musician and entrepreneur}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| Name = Jack Conte\n| Img = Jack_Conte_2014.jpg\n| Img_capt = Jack Conte in 2014\n| Img_size = 250\n| Background = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| Occupation = [[Singer-songwriter]], [[Multi-instrumentalist]], [[Record producer|Producer]], [[Entrepreneur]]\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1984|7|12}}\n| instrument = [[Singing|Vocals]], [[guitar]], [[piano]], [[Organ (music)|organ]], [[Keyboard instrument|keyboards]], [[bass guitar]], [[drums]], percussion, [[accordion]]\n| birth_place = [[San Francisco]], [[California]], U.S.\n| Birth_name = \n| Alias = \n| Genre = {{flatlist|\n* [[Jazz fusion]]\n* [[synthpop]]\n* [[alternative rock]]\n* [[indie music|indie]]\n* [[contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n* [[power pop]]\n* [[Funk music|funk]]\n}}\n| Years_active = 2002\u2013present\n| Associated_acts = [[Pomplamoose]], [[Nataly Dawn]], [[Julia Nunes]], Wade Johnston, [[Knower|KNOWER]], Louis Cole, [[Ben Grant]], [[Foxtails Brigade]], Danielle ate the Sandwich, Lauren O'Connell, Ryan Lerman, My Terrible Friend, Carlos Cabrera, [[Project RnL]], Scary Pockets\n| URL = [http://www.jackcontemusic.com/ Official website]\n}}\n'''Jack Conte''' ({{IPAc-en|\u02c8|k|\u0252|n|t|i}}; born July 12, 1984) is an American musician, [[singer-songwriter]], [[disc jockey]], [[entrepreneur]], and [[filmmaker]]. He is one half of the band [[Pomplamoose]],<ref name=\"tri\">{{Triangulation|150|Jack Conte}}</ref> along with his wife [[Nataly Dawn]], as well as being CEO and co-founder of [[Patreon]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/kathleenchaykowski/2018/02/13/digital-medici-how-this-musician-turned-entrepreneur-plans-to-save-creators-from-advertising/#43804f871313|title=How This Musician-Turned-Entrepreneur Plans To Save Creators From Advertising|last=Chaykowski|first=Kathleen|date=13 February 2018|access-date=10 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nConte has recorded two [[Extended play|EP]]s \u2014 ''Sleep in Color'' and ''Nightmares and Daydreams'' \u2014 and released them along with the compilation ''VideoSongs Volume I'' through the [[iTunes Store]].<ref name=\"adequacy\">{{cite web|title = Jack Conte \u2013 Sleep in Color EP| publisher     = DOA| date          = October 13, 2008| url           = http://www.adequacy.net/2009/03/jack-conte-sleep-in-color-ep/| accessdate    = July 25, 2009}}</ref>  Conte's use of [[Electro-Harmonix]] audio equipment has been featured by the company in several different videos.<ref name=\"ehx\">{{cite web| title         = Voice Box Demo by Jack Conte and Nataly Dawn| publisher     = [[Electro-Harmonix]]| date          = January 6, 2009| url           = http://www.ehx.com/blog/voice-box-demo-by-jack-conte-and-nataly-dawn| accessdate    = July 25, 2009}}</ref><ref name=\"gearwire\">{{cite web\n| title         = Electro-Harmonix Tube Zipper Soups The Heck Out Of Jack Conte's Martin| publisher     = Gearwire\n| date          = June 24, 2009| url           = http://www.gearwire.com/electroharmonix-tubezipper-reviewjackconte.html\n| access-date    = March 2, 2014| archive-url    = https://web.archive.org/web/20121123232944/http://www.gearwire.com/electroharmonix-tubezipper-reviewjackconte.html| archive-date   = November 23, 2012| url-status       = dead}}</ref><ref name=\"gearwire2\">{{cite web\n |title=Electro-Harmonix Bass MicroSynth Makes Some Amazing Low End For Jack Conte of Pomplamoose \n |publisher=Gearwire \n |date=June 24, 2009 \n |url=http://www.gearwire.com/electroharmonix-bassmicrosynth-reviewjackconte.html \n |access-date=March 2, 2014 \n |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121123231024/http://www.gearwire.com/electroharmonix-bassmicrosynth-reviewjackconte.html \n |archive-date=November 23, 2012 \n |url-status=dead \n |df= \n}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nConte's first notable appearance in mainstream media was when he supplied his voice for the \"teenage boy\" character in the popular videogame ''[[The Sims 2]]''.<ref name=gamefaqs>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamefaqs.com/pc/914811-the-sims-2/data |title=The Sims 2 |work=GameFAQs |accessdate=June 13, 2010}}</ref>\n\nHe gained widespread attention when his video ''Yeah Yeah Yeah''<ref name=\"Jack Conte - Yeah Yeah Yeah\">\n{{cite web|title = Jack Conte - Yeah Yeah Yeah|publisher = Jack Conte| date = April 12, 2008| url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dzr32OqGlOA| accessdate = September 6, 2015}}</ref> was featured on YouTube's main page.<ref name=\"maneater\">{{cite web| title = Jack Conte gets emotional in new album| publisher = The Maneater| date = October 13, 2008| url = http://www.themaneater.com/stories/2008/10/13/Jack-Conte-gets-emotional-in-new-album/| accessdate = July 25, 2009| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090309214429/http://www.themaneater.com/stories/2008/10/13/Jack-Conte-gets-emotional-in-new-album/| archive-date = March 9, 2009| url-status = dead}}</ref> The video, animated in [[stop motion]], has been viewed over one million times.  The majority of his new music is released as singles posted to [[YouTube]].  These mostly take the form of \"VideoSongs\", a medium he defines with two rules:\n{{cquote|\n#What you see is what you hear. (No lip-syncing for instruments or voice)\n#If you hear it, at some point you see it. (No hidden sounds)}}\n\nConte formed the band [[Pomplamoose]] with [[Nataly Dawn]] in mid-2008.<ref name=\"brock\">\n{{cite web|title = Pomplamoose: your new favourite band| publisher = The Brock Press| url = http://media.www.brockpress.com/media/storage/paper384/news/2008/11/04/ArtsEntertainment/Pomplamoose.Your.New.Favourite.Band-3523536.shtml| access-date = March 2, 2014 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110102053135/http://media.www.brockpress.com/media/storage/paper384/news/2008/11/04/ArtsEntertainment/Pomplamoose.Your.New.Favourite.Band-3523536.shtml | archive-date = January 2, 2011 | url-status = dead}}</ref>  The band's presence is primarily online, having only performed a handful of live shows.  Nevertheless, the collaboration has garnered significant fan support.  Fueled by the feature of their video \"Hail Mary\" on the main page of YouTube, Pomplamoose's channel has 1 million subscribers. The duo produced the third studio album released by [[Julia Nunes]] in 2010.\n\nOn May 7, 2013, Conte announced the launch of [[Patreon]], a [[crowdfunding]] venture, together with co-founder Samuel Yam. The startup is \"like a [[kickstarter]] for people who release stuff on a regular basis.\"<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mZ02alEkbLw#t=4m10s Jack Conte - Pedals Music Video (featuring REAL robots)]\"</ref><ref name=wired>{{cite web |url=https://www.wired.com/2013/10/big-idea-patreon/ |title=The Next Big Thing You Missed: \u2018Eternal Kickstarter\u2019 Reinvents Indie Art |publisher=Wired |date=October 22, 2013 |accessdate=September 6, 2015 |author=Ryan Tate}}</ref>\n\nJack Conte also plays keyboards in the funk band [[Scary Pockets]].\n\nJack Conte has been identified as a \"Young Global Leader\" by World Economic Forum in 2020. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.weforum.org/agenda/2020/03/ygl-wef-young-global-leaders/|title=Meet the young leaders set to shape 2020|website=World Economic Forum}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nMuch of Conte's work has been met with positive reviews, citing evocative lyrics in ''Sleep in Color'',<ref name=\"maneater\"/> creative delivery of his videosongs,<ref name=\"antiquiet\">{{cite web | title = Breaking Ground With Jack Conte | publisher = Antiquiet | date = August 4, 2008 | url = http://www.antiquiet.com/interviews/2008/08/breaking-ground-with-jack-conte/ | accessdate = July 25, 2009}}</ref> and the tenacity to create his own niche in the Internet music market. However, Conte's music was reviewed less favorably by Amplifier magazine: \"Hints of [[Conor Oberst]], [[Radiohead]], [[Patrick Watson (musician)|Patrick Watson]], contemporary punk rock (screamo), radio power pop, and incalculable other singer songwriters are more than borrowed, making for a short mishmash of electro rock.\"<ref name=\"amplifier\">{{cite web | title = Jack Conte - Sleep in Color EP | publisher = Amplifier Magazine | date = January 12, 2009 | url = http://www.amplifiermagazine.com/reviews/cds/jack_conte_cd_ep.php| access-date = March 2, 2014 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20111111111311/http://amplifiermagazine.com/reviews/cds/jack_conte_cd_ep.php | archive-date = November 11, 2011 | url-status = dead}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nConte and [[Nataly Dawn]] became engaged in January 2016,<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WlCy0RNW9Ds</ref> and the two were married in May 2016.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ANX6tPlzxzU</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Albums===\n*''VideoSongs Volume 1''\n:*Release date: August 29, 2008\n:*Label: ShadowTree Music\n:*Format: [[Music download|Digital download]]\n#\"Push\"\n#\"Eat\"\n#\"These Days\"\n#\"The Giant\"\n#\"Lonely Ghost\"\n#\"Flavors\"\n#\"Passenger Seat\" (featuring [[Knower|Louis Cole]])\n#\"Yeah Yeah Yeah\"\n#\"Hail Mary\"\n#\"Be Still\"\n\n*''VideoSongs Volume 2''\n:*Release date: August 15, 2008\n:*Label: ShadowTree Music\n:*Format: [[Music download|Digital download]]\n#\"We Grew Up So Well\"\n#\"Kitchen Fork\"\n#\"This Disaster\"\n#\"Ten Thousand Feet Per Second\"\n#\"Out of Nowhere\"\n#\"Trains and Window Collection\"\n#\"Impression\"\n#\"On Planets\"\n#\"Gulf\"\n#\"I Know\"\n\n*''VS4''\n:*Release date: March 23, 2011\n:*Label: ShadowTree Music\n:*Format: [[Compact disc|CD]], [[Music download|Digital download]]\n#\"Make the Grade\"\n#\"Time of Your Life\"\n#\"Sinking Feeling\"\n#\"The Time Has Come\"\n#\"Off With His Head\"\n#\"Long Long Time Ago\"\n#\"Mercenary\"\n#\"Away\"\n#\"Only Dreaming\"\n#\"Get It Out\"\n#\"I Would Be Happy\"\n#\"I Wonder Where the Moments Go\"\n#\"Mister Money Bags\"\n#\"Push It\"\n#\"Reprise\"\n\n===Extended plays===\n*''Nightmares and Daydreams''\n:*Release date: May 21, 2007\n:*Label: ShadowTree Music\n:*Format: [[Music download|Digital download]]\n#\"Starlight\"\n#\"Tick Tock\"\n#\"Yeah Yeah Yeah\"\n#\"Unfrozen\"\n\n*''VideoSongs Volume 3''\n:*Release date July 13, 2008\n:*ShadowTree Music\n:*Format: [[Music download|Digital download]]\n#\"The Way It Was Before\"\n#\"Freaks and Clowns\"\n#\"Bloody Nose\"\n#\"Get Happy\"\n\n*''Sleep in Color''\n:*Release date: September 25, 2008\n:*Label: ShadowTree Music\n:*Format: [[Compact disc|CD]], [[Music download|Digital download]]\n#\"Hollywood Endings\"\n#\"Like a Match\"\n#\"The Greatest Hoax\"\n#\"Now That's Sacred\"\n#\"Carousel Waltz\"\n\n*''Conte''\n:*Release date: 2013\n:*Label: ShadowTree Music\n:*Format: [[Music download|Digital download]]\n#\"I Know Better\"\n#\"The World Is Easy\"\n#\"Pedals\"\n#\"Real DJ (V1)\"\n\n===Music videos===\n*\"Yeah Yeah Yeah\"\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://jackcontemusic.com/}}\n* [http://www.pomplamoose.com/ Pomplamoose official website]\n* [https://www.scarypocketsfunk.com/ Scary Pockets official website]\n* {{YouTube|user=jackcontemusic}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Pomplamoose}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Conte, Jack}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American guitarists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American keyboardists]]\n[[Category:21st-century accordionists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:American accordionists]]\n[[Category:American drummers]]\n[[Category:American multi-instrumentalists]]\n[[Category:American male guitarists]]\n[[Category:American male pianists]]\n[[Category:American male singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American percussionists]]\n[[Category:American ukulele players]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Guitarists from San Francisco]]\n[[Category:21st-century American pianists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American drummers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n[[Category:Male YouTubers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|American musician and entrepreneur}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| Name = Jack Conte\n| Img = Jack_Conte_2014.jpg\n| Img_capt = Jack Conte in 2014\n| Img_size = 250\n| Background = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n| Occupation = [[Singer-songwriter]], [[Multi-instrumentalist]], [[Record producer|Producer]], [[Entrepreneur]]\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1984|7|12}}\n| instrument = [[Singing|Vocals]], [[guitar]], [[piano]], [[Organ (music)|organ]], [[Keyboard instrument|keyboards]], [[bass guitar]], [[drums]], percussion, [[accordion]]\n| birth_place = [[San Francisco]], [[California]], U.S.\n| Birth_name = \n| Alias = \n| Genre = {{flatlist|\n* [[Jazz fusion]]\n* [[synthpop]]\n* [[alternative rock]]\n* [[indie music|indie]]\n* [[contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n* [[power pop]]\n* [[Funk music|funk]]\n}}\n| Years_active = 2002\u2013present\n| Associated_acts = [[Pomplamoose]], [[Nataly Dawn]], [[Julia Nunes]], Wade Johnston, [[Knower|KNOWER]], Louis Cole, [[Ben Grant]], [[Foxtails Brigade]], Danielle ate the Sandwich, Lauren O'Connell, Ryan Lerman, My Terrible Friend, Carlos Cabrera, [[Project RnL]], Scary Pockets\n| URL = [http://www.jackcontemusic.com/ Official website]\n}}\n'''Jack Conte''' ({{IPAc-en|\u02c8|k|\u0252|n|t|i}}; born July 12, 1984) is an American musician, [[singer-songwriter]], [[disc jockey]], [[entrepreneur]], and [[filmmaker]]. He is one half of the band [[Pomplamoose]],<ref name=\"tri\">{{Triangulation|150|Jack Conte}}</ref> along with his wife [[Nataly Dawn]], as well as being CEO and co-founder of [[Patreon]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/kathleenchaykowski/2018/02/13/digital-medici-how-this-musician-turned-entrepreneur-plans-to-save-creators-from-advertising/#43804f871313|title=How This Musician-Turned-Entrepreneur Plans To Save Creators From Advertising|last=Chaykowski|first=Kathleen|date=13 February 2018|access-date=10 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nConte has recorded two [[Extended play|EP]]s \u2014 ''Sleep in Color'' and ''Nightmares and Daydreams'' \u2014 and released them along with the compilation ''VideoSongs Volume I'' through the [[iTunes Store]].<ref name=\"adequacy\">{{cite web|title = Jack Conte \u2013 Sleep in Color EP| publisher     = DOA| date          = October 13, 2008| url           = http://www.adequacy.net/2009/03/jack-conte-sleep-in-color-ep/| accessdate    = July 25, 2009}}</ref>  Conte's use of [[Electro-Harmonix]] audio equipment has been featured by the company in several different videos.<ref name=\"ehx\">{{cite web| title         = Voice Box Demo by Jack Conte and Nataly Dawn| publisher     = [[Electro-Harmonix]]| date          = January 6, 2009| url           = http://www.ehx.com/blog/voice-box-demo-by-jack-conte-and-nataly-dawn| accessdate    = July 25, 2009}}</ref><ref name=\"gearwire\">{{cite web\n| title         = Electro-Harmonix Tube Zipper Soups The Heck Out Of Jack Conte's Martin| publisher     = Gearwire\n| date          = June 24, 2009| url           = http://www.gearwire.com/electroharmonix-tubezipper-reviewjackconte.html\n| access-date    = March 2, 2014| archive-url    = https://web.archive.org/web/20121123232944/http://www.gearwire.com/electroharmonix-tubezipper-reviewjackconte.html| archive-date   = November 23, 2012| url-status       = dead}}</ref><ref name=\"gearwire2\">{{cite web\n |title=Electro-Harmonix Bass MicroSynth Makes Some Amazing Low End For Jack Conte of Pomplamoose \n |publisher=Gearwire \n |date=June 24, 2009 \n |url=http://www.gearwire.com/electroharmonix-bassmicrosynth-reviewjackconte.html \n |access-date=March 2, 2014 \n |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121123231024/http://www.gearwire.com/electroharmonix-bassmicrosynth-reviewjackconte.html \n |archive-date=November 23, 2012 \n |url-status=dead \n |df= \n}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nConte's first notable appearance in mainstream media was when he supplied his voice for the \"teenage boy\" character in the popular videogame ''[[The Sims 2]]''.<ref name=gamefaqs>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamefaqs.com/pc/914811-the-sims-2/data |title=The Sims 2 |work=GameFAQs |accessdate=June 13, 2010}}</ref>\n\nHe gained widespread attention when his video ''Yeah Yeah Yeah''<ref name=\"Jack Conte - Yeah Yeah Yeah\">\n{{cite web|title = Jack Conte - Yeah Yeah Yeah|publisher = Jack Conte| date = April 12, 2008| url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dzr32OqGlOA| accessdate = September 6, 2015}}</ref> was featured on YouTube's main page.<ref name=\"maneater\">{{cite web| title = Jack Conte gets emotional in new album| publisher = The Maneater| date = October 13, 2008| url = http://www.themaneater.com/stories/2008/10/13/Jack-Conte-gets-emotional-in-new-album/| accessdate = July 25, 2009| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090309214429/http://www.themaneater.com/stories/2008/10/13/Jack-Conte-gets-emotional-in-new-album/| archive-date = March 9, 2009| url-status = dead}}</ref> The video, animated in [[stop motion]], has been viewed over one million times.  The majority of his new music is released as singles posted to [[YouTube]].  These mostly take the form of \"VideoSongs\", a medium he defines with two rules:\n{{cquote|\n#What you see is what you hear. (No lip-syncing for instruments or voice)\n#If you hear it, at some point you see it. (No hidden sounds)}}\n\nConte formed the band [[Pomplamoose]] with [[Nataly Dawn]] in mid-2008.<ref name=\"brock\">\n{{cite web|title = Pomplamoose: your new favourite band| publisher = The Brock Press| url = http://media.www.brockpress.com/media/storage/paper384/news/2008/11/04/ArtsEntertainment/Pomplamoose.Your.New.Favourite.Band-3523536.shtml| access-date = March 2, 2014 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110102053135/http://media.www.brockpress.com/media/storage/paper384/news/2008/11/04/ArtsEntertainment/Pomplamoose.Your.New.Favourite.Band-3523536.shtml | archive-date = January 2, 2011 | url-status = dead}}</ref>  The band's presence is primarily online, having only performed a handful of live shows.  Nevertheless, the collaboration has garnered significant fan support.  Fueled by the feature of their video \"Hail Mary\" on the main page of YouTube, Pomplamoose's channel has nearly 900,000 subscribers. The duo produced the third studio album released by [[Julia Nunes]] in 2010.\n\nOn May 7, 2013, Conte announced the launch of [[Patreon]], a [[crowdfunding]] venture, together with co-founder Samuel Yam. The startup is \"like a [[kickstarter]] for people who release stuff on a regular basis.\"<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mZ02alEkbLw#t=4m10s Jack Conte - Pedals Music Video (featuring REAL robots)]\"</ref><ref name=wired>{{cite web |url=https://www.wired.com/2013/10/big-idea-patreon/ |title=The Next Big Thing You Missed: \u2018Eternal Kickstarter\u2019 Reinvents Indie Art |publisher=Wired |date=October 22, 2013 |accessdate=September 6, 2015 |author=Ryan Tate}}</ref>\n\nJack Conte also plays keyboards in the funk band [[Scary Pockets]].\n\nJack Conte has been identified as a \"Young Global Leader\" by World Economic Forum in 2020. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.weforum.org/agenda/2020/03/ygl-wef-young-global-leaders/|title=Meet the young leaders set to shape 2020|website=World Economic Forum}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nMuch of Conte's work has been met with positive reviews, citing evocative lyrics in ''Sleep in Color'',<ref name=\"maneater\"/> creative delivery of his videosongs,<ref name=\"antiquiet\">{{cite web | title = Breaking Ground With Jack Conte | publisher = Antiquiet | date = August 4, 2008 | url = http://www.antiquiet.com/interviews/2008/08/breaking-ground-with-jack-conte/ | accessdate = July 25, 2009}}</ref> and the tenacity to create his own niche in the Internet music market. However, Conte's music was reviewed less favorably by Amplifier magazine: \"Hints of [[Conor Oberst]], [[Radiohead]], [[Patrick Watson (musician)|Patrick Watson]], contemporary punk rock (screamo), radio power pop, and incalculable other singer songwriters are more than borrowed, making for a short mishmash of electro rock.\"<ref name=\"amplifier\">{{cite web | title = Jack Conte - Sleep in Color EP | publisher = Amplifier Magazine | date = January 12, 2009 | url = http://www.amplifiermagazine.com/reviews/cds/jack_conte_cd_ep.php| access-date = March 2, 2014 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20111111111311/http://amplifiermagazine.com/reviews/cds/jack_conte_cd_ep.php | archive-date = November 11, 2011 | url-status = dead}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nConte and [[Nataly Dawn]] became engaged in January 2016,<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WlCy0RNW9Ds</ref> and the two were married in May 2016.<ref>https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ANX6tPlzxzU</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Albums===\n*''VideoSongs Volume 1''\n:*Release date: August 29, 2008\n:*Label: ShadowTree Music\n:*Format: [[Music download|Digital download]]\n#\"Push\"\n#\"Eat\"\n#\"These Days\"\n#\"The Giant\"\n#\"Lonely Ghost\"\n#\"Flavors\"\n#\"Passenger Seat\" (featuring [[Knower|Louis Cole]])\n#\"Yeah Yeah Yeah\"\n#\"Hail Mary\"\n#\"Be Still\"\n\n*''VideoSongs Volume 2''\n:*Release date: August 15, 2008\n:*Label: ShadowTree Music\n:*Format: [[Music download|Digital download]]\n#\"We Grew Up So Well\"\n#\"Kitchen Fork\"\n#\"This Disaster\"\n#\"Ten Thousand Feet Per Second\"\n#\"Out of Nowhere\"\n#\"Trains and Window Collection\"\n#\"Impression\"\n#\"On Planets\"\n#\"Gulf\"\n#\"I Know\"\n\n*''VS4''\n:*Release date: March 23, 2011\n:*Label: ShadowTree Music\n:*Format: [[Compact disc|CD]], [[Music download|Digital download]]\n#\"Make the Grade\"\n#\"Time of Your Life\"\n#\"Sinking Feeling\"\n#\"The Time Has Come\"\n#\"Off With His Head\"\n#\"Long Long Time Ago\"\n#\"Mercenary\"\n#\"Away\"\n#\"Only Dreaming\"\n#\"Get It Out\"\n#\"I Would Be Happy\"\n#\"I Wonder Where the Moments Go\"\n#\"Mister Money Bags\"\n#\"Push It\"\n#\"Reprise\"\n\n===Extended plays===\n*''Nightmares and Daydreams''\n:*Release date: May 21, 2007\n:*Label: ShadowTree Music\n:*Format: [[Music download|Digital download]]\n#\"Starlight\"\n#\"Tick Tock\"\n#\"Yeah Yeah Yeah\"\n#\"Unfrozen\"\n\n*''VideoSongs Volume 3''\n:*Release date July 13, 2008\n:*ShadowTree Music\n:*Format: [[Music download|Digital download]]\n#\"The Way It Was Before\"\n#\"Freaks and Clowns\"\n#\"Bloody Nose\"\n#\"Get Happy\"\n\n*''Sleep in Color''\n:*Release date: September 25, 2008\n:*Label: ShadowTree Music\n:*Format: [[Compact disc|CD]], [[Music download|Digital download]]\n#\"Hollywood Endings\"\n#\"Like a Match\"\n#\"The Greatest Hoax\"\n#\"Now That's Sacred\"\n#\"Carousel Waltz\"\n\n*''Conte''\n:*Release date: 2013\n:*Label: ShadowTree Music\n:*Format: [[Music download|Digital download]]\n#\"I Know Better\"\n#\"The World Is Easy\"\n#\"Pedals\"\n#\"Real DJ (V1)\"\n\n===Music videos===\n*\"Yeah Yeah Yeah\"\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://jackcontemusic.com/}}\n* [http://www.pomplamoose.com/ Pomplamoose official website]\n* [https://www.scarypocketsfunk.com/ Scary Pockets official website]\n* {{YouTube|user=jackcontemusic}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Pomplamoose}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Conte, Jack}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century American guitarists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American keyboardists]]\n[[Category:21st-century accordionists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:American accordionists]]\n[[Category:American drummers]]\n[[Category:American multi-instrumentalists]]\n[[Category:American male guitarists]]\n[[Category:American male pianists]]\n[[Category:American male singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:American percussionists]]\n[[Category:American ukulele players]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Guitarists from San Francisco]]\n[[Category:21st-century American pianists]]\n[[Category:21st-century American drummers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n[[Catego